places:
    place-summerhall:
        name: "Summerhall"
        type: ruin
        parent: place-the-stormlands
        notes: "A ruined Targaryen palace in the Stormlands near the Dornish Marches. Destroyed by a great fire in 259 AC, the Tragedy at Summerhall, in which King Aegon V and others perished. Rhaegar Targaryen was born on the same day."
